<h2 id="registering-for-an-account-and-initial-setup">Registering for an Account and Initial Setup</h2>
<p>The following steps are required before launching an app in the Pi Ecosystem. Once these steps are completed a developer can choose their development path.</p>

<ol>
  <li><strong>Download the Pi App</strong></li>
  <li>Register for an account</li>
  <li><strong>Download and Sign into the Pi Browser</strong></li>
  <li><strong>Verify Email Address</strong></li>
  <li><strong>Create a Pi Wallet</strong></li>
</ol>

<h2 id="initial-setup-and-pi-sandbox-launch">Initial Setup and Pi Sandbox Launch</h2>
<ol>
  <li><strong>Register your App</strong></li>
  <li><strong>Configure App Hosting</strong></li>
  <li><strong>Read Documentation and Review Demo App</strong></li>
  <li><strong>Configure your Appâ€™s Development URL</strong></li>
  <li><strong>Run your development App in the sandbox</strong></li>
</ol>

<h2 id="deploy-app-on-pi-testnet">Deploy App on Pi Testnet</h2>
<ol>
  <li><strong>Deploy your app in a production environment</strong></li>
  <li><strong>Validate Domain Ownership</strong></li>
  <li><strong>Process a transaction on your app</strong></li>
</ol>

<h2 id="launching-on-pi-mainnet">Launching on Pi Mainnet</h2>
<ol>
  <li>Obtain a Mainnet Wallet</li>
  <li>Create a Developer Portal Project directed at the Pi Mainnet</li>
  <li>Verify App URL</li>
  <li>Generate API Key</li>
  <li>Launch App and complete a Pi payment</li>
</ol>
